      "body": "Thanks for taking a look. I'm not sure it was intentional. `generatetodescriptor` rejects negative values via `self.Arg<uint64_t>()`, so if the wrapping behavior in `generatetoaddress` were by design I'd expect the newer sibling RPC to preserve it rather than diverge.\r\n\r\nWould you prefer I reframe the PR description as a consistency cleanup rather than a bugfix if that better reflects how the project wants to categorise it?",
